                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Greetings,
<br />

<br />
I have always been interested in playing an enchanter (my main is a wizard) and have decided that I am going to give it a go soon.
<br />

<br />
From an end game perspective, would it be better to put starting points into stamina for some extra hit points in the high levels, rather than int or charisma? I know as a wizard that my int was very easy to max out, and am wondering how easy it is to max int AND charisma out as an enchanter through decent buyable gear. No drop raid gear won't be an option for this character for a long time most likely, so I'll have to content myself with buying stuff or picking up gear along the way. Cash in game isn't much of a limiting factor however so I should be able to gear up an enchanter pretty well depending on availability of stuff for sale.
<br />

<br />
So, essentially, I'm wondering if stamina would be a better choice for my starting points rather than int or charisma given my ability to buy good gear right from the get go.
<br />

<br />
Any constructive comments are greatly appreciated.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
