                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">There isn't much reason to put points into stamina.  The conversation rate for casters is so low.  You can max the sta, but you'll wind up paying for it in the wearing of gear just for cha.  Gear that, if you replaced with something worn for hp, would net you more hp.
<br />

<br />
Take a look at the likes of earthweave.  The best buyable armor we can get at the moment.  No cha.  Look at ornate, which you'll want bracers and arms from for the effects...low stats.  High end LDoN stuff (if you go that route) has lots of raw hp, but you can only use an 8 cha/int, 10 cha, and 10 int augs 1x, as they are lore.
<br />

<br />
A lot of gear will be made for all people.  A lot for all int casters.  But cha will always be lacking on most of that gear, leading to a few items who's only redeeming value is a lot of cha, lacking in everything else you would want.  Well, up until high end raid gear, of course.
<br />

<br />
In short, the more freedom you can get by not having to choose gear for cha, the better off you are.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
