                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Don't forget that the Jewelcraft trophy is emminently doable and affordable compared to about all the other tradeskill trophies, most especially for an enchanter (and now with the mass enchant spells that I never got to use when I was skilling up *leer*).  For now, my 
<br />

<br />
Grandmaster Jeweler's Eyeglass
<br />
LORE ITEM  NO DROP  
<br />
Slot: PRIMARY  SECONDARY  RANGE  AMMO  
<br />
Skill Mod: Jewellery +5 %
<br />
STR: +10  CHA: +50  WIS: +10  INT: +10  
<br />
Effect: Grandmaster's Satchel (Must Equip. Casting Time: 10.0)
<br />
WT:  0.1    Size: SMALL
<br />

<br />
is parked in my range slot (remember no stat bonus if it is in your ammo slot).  If you want to do another tradeskill though, take your pick, the stats are the same.  50 charisma plus self buffing is enough to overcome any charisma gear shortcomings and keep my charisma higher than it really even needs to be.  Stick with good HP gear as you can find it; I invested all my savings and KEI booty in that and have not been disappointed.  Lots of HP and now Arcane Rune have given me a much-needed confidence, especially in charming, that was lacking in my playstyle.  Risk aversion can keep you alive.  (Intelligent) risk taking can keep you involved, excited, and impressive.  The more hp you have, the more risks you can afford to take.
<br />

<br />
That was off topic though, sorry.  Anyway, I think I put all of my available stats into charisma and the rest into intelligence, on the advice of my friend who had no idea what he was talking about.  Maybe not the best decision but then again maybe so, since gear with int is much more plentiful than charisma.  I've been impressed with the high level of charisma I've maintained through self-buffing, the charisma I rolled, and then when I got my trophy around level 52 I got a lot of flexibility I lacked before.  I could ditch my old charisma gear for stuff that had what I really wanted.  At the time that was intelligence but now I am convinced that HP &gt; all.  Besides, alot or most gear with HP has mana on it too, which is just icing on the cake.  =)  And stamina while nice doesn't translate to much HP anyway.
<br />

<br />
In the end, put the points where you want them.  If you have money to burn it won't make much of a difference anyway.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=646635" target="_blank" class="postlink">Saediien Iluvatri</a>
<br />
Phantasmist/Circle of the Golden Dragon/The Rathe</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
